---
import SiteLayout from '../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
---
<SiteLayout title="Notes - Simon Gelbart" current="notes">
  <section class="page-heading narrow">
    <p class="eyebrow">Notes</p>
    <h1>Cross-project engineering notes.</h1>
    <p class="lede">Global notes are for themes that cut across projects. Project-specific decisions stay with the project documentation.</p>
  </section>
  <section class="section split">
    <div><p class="eyebrow">Planned notes</p><h2>Topics to write next</h2></div>
    <ul class="feature-list">
      <li>Why Pattrn keeps routing outside the core</li>
      <li>Why LORQ is not an LLM benchmark</li>
      <li>Designing small backend tools with explicit boundaries</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
